    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense for the cultural preservation angle. To really nail the debate, I also need to prepare for the economic or logistical arguments. Sometimes people argue that segregation actually benefits the community by concentrating resources or creating specialized economic ecosystems. \n\nCan you expand on that? Like, could you provide a more detailed argument for how separating communities might actually lead to better economic stability or more efficient resource management for specific groups? I want to make sure my points sound logically sound and not just like vague platitudes.",
